org_admin_settings.enterprise_installer_.string: For users on the Enterprise Plan, Figma provides a machine-wide MSI installer for Windows. This MSI will install Figma in Program Files for all users of a machine, and will not automatically update itself.
For users on the Enterprise Plan, Figma provides a PKG installer for macOS.
See our Help Center for more information.

org_settings.external_collaboration_cont.string: This setting affects people's access to content, so you may want to {let_org_know} before making updates.
When you limit access to content from outside {orgName}, members {cannot}:
When you allow members to access content from outside {orgName}, they can:
Accept invites from other teams and organizations to join files, projects, or teams
Edit or comment on files and drafts that have been shared with them from other teams and organizations ({note} files will be view-only)
View, comment on, or edit files and drafts that have been shared with them from other teams and organizations
Create drafts, files, or projects in other teams or organizations
Have edit access in other teams' or organizations' open sessions while logged in
Members can access content from outside {orgName}
Changed content access setting. This may take up to 10 minutes to update.

org_settings.guest_control.guest_definit.string: Guests are external users without an {domains} address who join your organization.

org_settings.guest_control.guest_questio.string: Who can join your organization as a guest?

org_settings.guest_control.link_sharing_.string: Public link sharing is currently {enabled} in your organization, which means external users may still be able to view content through a link if the individual file permissions allow it. You can turn this off in your {publicLinkSharingSettings}.

org_settings.guest_control.no_guest_conf.string: Users will no longer be able to share public links with “can edit” permissions. Any existing public links with “can edit” permissions will be downgraded to “can view” permissions.
